This topic describes how to patch <%= vars.product_full %> Management Console (<%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> MC) deployment components.  


<br>
<br>
## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

You can use <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> Management Console to individually update some of the components of your deployment when a new minor version of those components is available. 
For more information, see [Update <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> MC Deployment Components](#update-components) below.  


<br>
<br>
## <a id='update-components'></a>Update <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> MC Deployment Components

To update a <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> MC deployment component:  

1. In <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> MC, go to **Configuration** &gt; **<%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> Component Patch** to view the list of components that are ready for patching.  
1. Obtain the patch installers.  
    * In air-gapped environments, download the patch installer from https://downloads.vmware.com/ to a local location. Click the **Import Patch** button to upload the installer to the management console.  
    * In environments with access to the internet, click the **Download** button next to the relevant components to import the patch installers directly.  
    ![Import patches](images/console/import-patches.png)  
1. When the patch imports are complete, select **Install Patch** to patch a component.  
    ![Install patches](images/console/install-patch.png)  
    
    If you are patching <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> MC itself, you will be automatically logged out during the patching process.   
1. Log back in to the <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> MC.  
1. Click the help icon `?` in the top banner and select **About** to check that the version of <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> MC has been updated.  
1. Click **TKG Integrated Edition** to check the versions of the installed components.  